text.tspan: Simple War
a 10-minute board game for two
to six players
EQUIPMENT:
You will need at least one six-sided die, and
two markers for each player. Dice make the
best markers.
HOW TO PLAY:
Players start by putting thier two markers on
one of the spaces with stars, claiming it as
their base. Each marker represents a tank,
which can move, repair itself, and attack. Put
a flag marker on the spot with a flag.
WINNING:
The goal is to capture the flag and move it to
your base. Each round, all players roll, and
the highest roll goes first. In her turn, each
player does something with all of her tanks.
MOVING:
Each tank starts with 3 hit points. If a tank
goes to 0 hit points, it explodes and is
removed from the board. Each turn, each
tank can move or repair itself. If it moves, it
can move up to one space for each of its hit
points. If it repairs, it gains 2 hit points, to a
maximum of 6. If you are using dice as mark
ers, turn each die to show its hit points!
COMBAT:
During her turn, each tank can attack once,
but it need not. Each tank’s attack range is
equal to its number of hit points. If the player
decides to attack, both players roll to see
who attacks first, then each rolls once to
determine damage. If the first roller kills the
second, the second loses his roll. The tank
being attacked may always return fire.
When the tank carrying the flag is killed, the
flag moves to tank that killed it.
Corners indicate 10”x14”
standard placemat size
